[PT] MrFlufffyLion 18-Dec-21 05:35 PM
PIEDMONT TRIBE "at the foot of the mountains." Long ago before any town had been established in the west was the Piedmont Tribe. They hunted, gathered, and wandered peacefully through the land. Then came men from the east with strange machines. They built weird-shaped buildings in the prairie and long railroads with steam engines. The Piedmont tribe still lives while hiding, surviving, and fighting for their tribe, territory, and culture. Founded in the September of 2019, right at the week when the faction update was released, the Piedmont Tribe came into existence. Originally named the Thunder Tribe, they changed to Ponderosa Tribe before deciding on their current name. The name's origins itself come from a history/geography book. In the year 2020, the legacy of the faction began. Great rallies, fun events, as well as Halloween and Christmas update play-throughs were only a tiny portion of what they did during that time. But soon Comanche started attempting to get them to merge, and when they battled with them they lost. Merging into them for a few months as the Bear Clan, they eventually fell into inactivity and disbanded. But now the rebirth of the Piedmont Tribe has begun. Behold our golden age, we will live on! "THE UNITED STATES MARSHALS ARE NOW RECRUITING"
We are the United States Marshals Service. We pride ourselves on being an elite fighting force that can and has faced whatever has come our way. Through our skill, leadership, communication, and tactics we have fought and won battles against the odds, and put up stalwart resistance against enemies that outnumber us 3:1, and we have won every war we have fought. Our selective application process has allowed us to admit only those worthy of calling themselves a Marshal into our ranks. So tell us. Do you have what it takes to become a United States Marshal?
[Requirements:]
- Ability to be in Voice Communications in game. - Must have a good horse. (Mustang or American Quarterhorse encouraged) - Decent at combat - A IQ at or above 100. - Activity (Attend at least two events every week.) - Ability to follow orders quickly and efficiently.
+ Benefits:
+ Free Black Market Supplies + A good group of friends. + Daily Patrols. + Joining a faction with the capability of holding two forts at once while they are being assaulted + An excellent environment to hone your skills. + Tier 3 Nitro Boost Rewards
[Wars]
+ Battle of Pinewood - USMS vs Eternal Raiders 2-0, USMS Victory. Numbers: 7 USMS. 7 ER. + Battle of Fort Henry - USMS vs Falcone Crime Syndicate 2-0, USMS Victory. Numbers: 5 USMS. 6 FCS
[Battles]
- Battle of Fort Henry - USMS vs Sweaty Rats, Pyrrhic Sweaty Rats Victory. Numbers: 4 USMS vs 11 SRs + Second Battle of Fort Henry - USMS vs Outcasts, Close USMS Victory. Numbers: 5 USMS vs 7 Outcasts + Battle of District 1 - USMS vs Mafia Italiana, Decisive USMS Victory. Numbers: 5 USMS vs 6 MIs
Do your duty to Civilized Society, and uphold law and order with the finest LEO Agency in the Wild West.

[PT] MrFlufffyLion 24-Dec-21 03:08 PM
PIEDMONT TRIBE "at the foot of the mountains." Long ago before any town had been established in the west was the Piedmont Tribe. They hunted, gathered, and wandered peacefully through the land. Then came men from the east with strange machines. They built weird-shaped buildings in the prairie and long railroads with steam engines. The Piedmont tribe still lives while hiding, surviving, and fighting for their tribe, territory, and culture. Founded in the September of 2019, right at the week when the faction update was released, the Piedmont Tribe came into existence. Originally named the Thunder Tribe, they changed to Ponderosa Tribe before deciding on their current name. The name's origins itself come from a history/geography book. In the year 2020, the legacy of the faction began. Great rallies, fun events, as well as Halloween and Christmas update play-throughs were only a tiny portion of what they did during that time. But soon Comanche started attempting to get them to merge, and when they battled with them they lost. Merging into them for a few months as the Bear Clan, they eventually fell into inactivity and disbanded. But now the rebirth of the Piedmont Tribe has begun. Behold our golden age, we will live on! [PT] MrFlufffyLion 29-Dec-21 05:26 PM
PIEDMONT TRIBE "at the foot of the mountains." Long ago before any town had been established in the west was the Piedmont Tribe. They hunted, gathered, and wandered peacefully through the land. Then came men from the east with strange machines. They built weird-shaped buildings in the prairie and long railroads with steam engines. The Piedmont tribe still lives while hiding, surviving, and fighting for their tribe, territory, and culture. Founded in the September of 2019, right at the week when the faction update was released, the Piedmont Tribe came into existence. Originally named the Thunder Tribe, they changed to Ponderosa Tribe before deciding on their current name. The name's origins itself come from a history/geography book. In the year 2020, the legacy of the faction began. Great rallies, fun events, as well as Halloween and Christmas update play-throughs were only a tiny portion of what they did during that time. But soon Comanche started attempting to get them to merge, and when they battled with them they lost. Merging into them for a few months as the Bear Clan, they eventually fell into inactivity and disbanded. But now the rebirth of the Piedmont Tribe has begun. Behold our golden age, we will live on! Benefits: â€¢ An active group. â€¢ Fun and friendly community. â€¢ Fun and engaging events â€¢ Fun bots, channels, and game nights. â€¢ New people to meet and all sorts of things to do! "THE UNITED STATES MARSHALS ARE NOW RECRUITING"
+ NOTICE: For the first week of January, January 1st through Janurary 8th, The Application requirement will be waived to all incoming recruits. Take advantage of the oppertunity while you can.
We are the United States Marshals Service. We pride ourselves on being an elite fighting force that can and has faced whatever has come our way. Through our skill, leadership, communication, and tactics we have fought and won battles against the odds, and put up stalwart resistance against enemies that outnumber us 3:1, and we have won every war we have fought. Our selective application process has allowed us to admit only those worthy of calling themselves a Marshal into our ranks. So tell us. Do you have what it takes to become a United States Marshal?
[Requirements:]
- Ability to be in Voice Communications in game. - Must have a good horse. (Mustang or American Quarterhorse encouraged) - Decent at combat - A IQ at or above 100. - Activity (Attend at least two events every week.) - Ability to follow orders quickly and efficiently.
+ Benefits:
+ Free Black Market Supplies + A good group of friends. + Daily Patrols. + Joining a faction with the capability of holding two forts at once while they are being assaulted + An excellent environment to hone your skills. + Tier 3 Nitro Boost Rewards + A faction undefeated in war.
[Wars]
+ Battle of Pinewood - USMS vs Eternal Raiders 2-0, USMS Victory. Numbers: 7 USMS. 7 ER. + Battle of Fort Henry - USMS vs Falcone Crime Syndicate 2-0, USMS Victory. Numbers: 5 USMS. 6 FCS + Battle of Callahan Manor - USMS vs Piedmont Tribe, USMS Victory.
[Battles]
- Battle of Fort Henry - USMS vs Sweaty Rats, Pyrrhic Sweaty Rats Victory. Numbers: 4 USMS vs 11 SRs + Second Battle of Fort Henry - USMS vs Outcasts, Close USMS Victory. Numbers: 5 USMS vs 7 Outcasts + Battle of District 1 - USMS vs Mafia Italiana, Decisive USMS Victory. Numbers: 5 USMS vs 6 MIs + Third Battle of Fort Henry - USMS vs Outcasts, Bleeding Falcons. Close USMS Victory. Numbers: 4 USMS vs 5 OC, BF, Varied others.
Do your duty to Civilized Society, and uphold law and order with the finest LEO Agency in the Wild West.

[PT] MrFlufffyLion 03-Jan-22 05:36 PM
PIEDMONT TRIBE "at the foot of the mountains." Long ago before any town had been established in the west was the Piedmont Tribe. They hunted, gathered, and wandered peacefully through the land. Then came men from the east with strange machines. They built weird-shaped buildings in the prairie and long railroads with steam engines. The Piedmont tribe still lives while hiding, surviving, and fighting for their tribe, territory, and culture. Founded in the September of 2019, right at the week when the faction update was released, the Piedmont Tribe came into existence. Originally named the Thunder Tribe, they changed to Ponderosa Tribe before deciding on their current name. The name's origins itself come from a history/geography book. In the year 2020, the legacy of the faction began. Great rallies, fun events, as well as Halloween and Christmas update play-throughs were only a tiny portion of what they did during that time. But soon Comanche started attempting to get them to merge, and when they battled with them they lost. Merging into them for a few months as the Bear Clan, they eventually fell into inactivity and disbanded. But now the rebirth of the Piedmont Tribe has begun. Behold our golden age, we will live on! Benefits: â€¢ An active group. â€¢ Fun and friendly community. â€¢ Fun and engaging events â€¢ Fun bots, channels, and game nights. â€¢ New people to meet and all sorts of things to do! PIEDMONT TRIBE "at the foot of the mountains." Long ago before any town had been established in the west was the Piedmont Tribe. They hunted, gathered, and wandered peacefully through the land. Then came men from the east with strange machines. They built weird-shaped buildings in the prairie and long railroads with steam engines. The Piedmont tribe still lives while hiding, surviving, and fighting for their tribe, territory, and culture. Founded in the September of 2019, right at the week when the faction update was released, the Piedmont Tribe came into existence. Originally named the Thunder Tribe, they changed to Ponderosa Tribe before deciding on their current name. The name's origins itself come from a history/geography book. In the year 2020, the legacy of the faction began. Great rallies, fun events, as well as Halloween and Christmas update play-throughs were only a tiny portion of what they did during that time. But soon Comanche started attempting to get them to merge, and when they battled with them they lost. Merging into them for a few months as the Bear Clan, they eventually fell into inactivity and disbanded. But now the rebirth of the Piedmont Tribe has begun. Behold our golden age, we will live on! PIEDMONT TRIBE "at the foot of the mountains." Long ago before any town had been established in the west was the Piedmont Tribe. They hunted, gathered, and wandered peacefully through the land. Then came men from the east with strange machines. They built weird-shaped buildings in the prairie and long railroads with steam engines. The Piedmont tribe still lives while hiding, surviving, and fighting for their tribe, territory, and culture. Founded in the September of 2019, right at the week when the faction update was released, the Piedmont Tribe came into existence. Originally named the Thunder Tribe, they changed to Ponderosa Tribe before deciding on their current name. The name's origins itself come from a history/geography book. In the year 2020, the legacy of the faction began. Great rallies, fun events, as well as Halloween and Christmas update play-throughs were only a tiny portion of what they did during that time. But soon Comanche started attempting to get them to merge, and when they battled with them they lost. Merging into them for a few months as the Bear Clan, they eventually fell into inactivity and disbanded. But now the rebirth of the Piedmont Tribe has begun. Behold our golden age, we will live on! PIEDMONT TRIBE "at the foot of the mountains." Long ago before any town had been established in the west was the Piedmont Tribe. They hunted, gathered, and wandered peacefully through the land. Then came men from the east with strange machines. They built weird-shaped buildings in the prairie and long railroads with steam engines. The Piedmont tribe still lives while hiding, surviving, and fighting for their tribe, territory, and culture. Founded in the September of 2019, right at the week when the faction update was released, the Piedmont Tribe came into existence. Originally named the Thunder Tribe, they changed to Ponderosa Tribe before deciding on their current name. The name's origins itself come from a history/geography book. In the year 2020, the legacy of the faction began. Great rallies, fun events, as well as Halloween and Christmas update play-throughs were only a tiny portion of what they did during that time. PIEDMONT TRIBE "at the foot of the mountains." Long ago before any town had been established in the west was the Piedmont Tribe. They hunted, gathered, and wandered peacefully through the land. Then came men from the east with strange machines. They built weird-shaped buildings in the prairie and long railroads with steam engines. The Piedmont tribe still lives while hiding, surviving, and fighting for their tribe, territory, and culture. Founded in the September of 2019, right at the week when the faction update was released, the Piedmont Tribe came into existence. Originally named the Thunder Tribe, they changed to Ponderosa Tribe before deciding on their current name. The name's origins itself come from a history/geography book. In the year 2020, the legacy of the faction began. Great rallies, fun events, as well as Halloween and Christmas update play-throughs were only a tiny portion of what they did during that time. But soon Comanche started attempting to get them to merge, and when they battled with them they lost. Merging into them for a few months as the Bear Clan, they eventually fell into inactivity and disbanded. But now the rebirth of the Piedmont Tribe has begun. Behold our golden age, we will live on! PIEDMONT TRIBE "at the foot of the mountains." Long ago before any town had been established in the west was the Piedmont Tribe. They hunted, gathered, and wandered peacefully through the land. Then came men from the east with strange machines. They built weird-shaped buildings in the prairie and long railroads with steam engines. The Piedmont tribe still lives while hiding, surviving, and fighting for their tribe, territory, and culture. Founded in the September of 2019, right at the week when the faction update was released, the Piedmont Tribe came into existence. Originally named the Thunder Tribe, they changed to Ponderosa Tribe before deciding on their current name. The name's origins itself come from a history/geography book. In the year 2020, the legacy of the faction began. Great rallies, fun events, as well as Halloween and Christmas update play-throughs were only a tiny portion of what they did during that time. But soon Comanche started attempting to get them to merge, and when they battled with them they lost. Merging into them for a few months as the Bear Clan, they eventually fell into inactivity and disbanded. But now the rebirth of the Piedmont Tribe has begun. Behold our golden age, we will live on! "THE UNITED STATES MARSHALS ARE NOW RECRUITING"
+ NOTICE: The Application requirement will be waived to all incoming recruits. Take advantage of the oppertunity while you can.
We are the United States Marshals Service. Through our skill, leadership, communication, and tactics we have fought and won battles against the odds, and put up stalwart resistance against enemies that outnumber us 3:1, and we have won every war we have fought. Our selective application process has allowed us to admit only those worthy of calling themselves a Marshal into our ranks. So tell us. Do you have what it takes to become a United States Marshal?
[Requirements:]
- Ability to be in Voice Communications - Must have a 3 Star Horse - Good at combat - Activity (Attend at least two events every week.) - Ability to follow orders.
+ Benefits:
+ A good group of friends. + An environment to hone your skills. + Tier 3 Nitro Boost Rewards + A faction undefeated in war.
[Wars]
+ Battle of Pinewood - USMS vs Eternal Raiders 2-0, USMS Victory. Numbers: 7 USMS. 7 ER. + Battle of Fort Henry - USMS vs Falcone Crime Syndicate 2-0, USMS Victory. Numbers: 5 USMS. 6 FCS
[Battles]
- Battle of Fort Henry - USMS vs Sweaty Rats, Pyrrhic Sweaty Rats Victory. Numbers: 4 USMS vs 11 SRs + Second Battle of Fort Henry - USMS vs Outcasts, Close USMS Victory. Numbers: 5 USMS vs 7 Outcasts + Battle of District 1 - USMS vs Mafia Italiana, Decisive USMS Victory. Numbers: 5 USMS vs 6 MIs + Third Battle of Fort Henry - USMS vs Outcasts, Bleeding Falcons. Close USMS Victory. Numbers: 4 USMS vs 5 OC, BF,
Do your duty to Civilized Society, and uphold law and order with the finest LEO Agency in the Wild West.

PIEDMONT TRIBE "at the foot of the mountains." Long ago before any town had been established in the west was the Piedmont Tribe. They hunted, gathered, and wandered peacefully through the land. Then came men from the east with strange machines. They built weird-shaped buildings in the prairie and long railroads with steam engines. The Piedmont tribe still lives while hiding, surviving, and fighting for their tribe, territory, and culture. Founded in the September of 2019, right at the week when the faction update was released, the Piedmont Tribe came into existence. Originally named the Thunder Tribe, they changed to Ponderosa Tribe before deciding on their current name. The name's origins itself come from a history/geography book. In the year 2020, the legacy of the faction began. Great rallies, fun events, as well as Halloween and Christmas update play-throughs were only a tiny portion of what they did during that time. But soon Comanche started attempting to get them to merge, and when they battled with them they lost. Merging into them for a few months as the Bear Clan, they eventually fell into inactivity and disbanded. But now the rebirth of the Piedmont Tribe has begun. Behold our golden age, we will live on! "THE UNITED STATES MARSHALS ARE NOW RECRUITING"
We hold the title of the longest running and most prestigious Federal Policing Agency in the Nation. Due to widespread lawlessness found in the Bronze City Area, the Marshals will be maintaining control of all Forts and of Bronze. In terms of our combat effectiveness, our battle record proves that even when we are severely outnumbered, we can deal heavy losses to our enemies.
[Requirements:]
- Ability to be in Voice Communications in game. - Must have a good horse. (Mustang or American Quarterhorse encouraged) - Decent at combat - A IQ at or above 100. - Activity (Attend at least two events every week.) - Ability to follow orders quickly and efficiently.
+ Benefits:
+ Free Black Market Supplies + A good group of friends. + Daily Patrols. + Joining a faction with the capability of holding two forts at once while they are being assaulted + An excellent environment to hone your skills.
[Wars]
+ Battle of Pinewood - USMS vs Eternal Raiders 2-0, USMS Victory. + War of the Great Desert - USMS vs Shadow Chaos Regiment, USMS Victory, SCR Retreat.
[Battles]
- Battle of Fort Henry - USMS vs Sweaty Rats, Pyrrhic Sweaty Rats Victory. Numbers: 4 USMS vs 11 SRs + Second Battle of Fort Henry - USMS vs Outcasts, Close USMS Victory. Numbers: 5 USMS vs 7 Outcasts + Battle of District 1 - USMS vs Mafia Italiana, Decisive USMS Victory. Numbers: 5 USMS vs 6 MIs
Do your duty to Civilized Society, and uphold law and order with the finest LEO Agency in the Wild West.

[PT] MrFlufffyLion 04-Feb-22 02:19 PM
PIEDMONT TRIBE "at the foot of the mountains." Long ago before any town had been established in the west was the Piedmont Tribe. They hunted, gathered, and wandered peacefully through the land. Then came men from the east with strange machines. They built weird-shaped buildings in the prairie and long railroads with steam engines. The Piedmont tribe still lives while hiding, surviving, and fighting for their tribe, territory, and culture. Founded in the September of 2019, right at the week when the faction update was released, the Piedmont Tribe came into existence. Originally named the Thunder Tribe, they changed to Ponderosa Tribe before deciding on their current name. The name's origins itself come from a history/geography book. In the year 2020, the legacy of the faction began. Great rallies, fun events, as well as Halloween and Christmas update play-throughs were only a tiny portion of what they did during that time. But soon Comanche started attempting to get them to merge, and when they battled with them they lost. Merging into them for a few months as the Bear Clan, they eventually fell into inactivity and disbanded. But now the rebirth of the Piedmont Tribe has begun. Behold our golden age, we will live on! [T.G.M.B] Fx 13-Feb-22 05:56 AM
TGMB TGMB or better known as The Green Mountain Boys was founded in late December of 2019 by Sharpsteer. We're based off of the real life militia which helped the United States gain independence back during the American revolution. We are the oldest TWW faction still out there. We know the ropes of the community. The difference between our faction and everyone else's is that we strain all toxicity and our main goal is to have fun, while still being able to be strong in battle. We host often events and raids, and we have gamenights every now and then so you can play with the members and focus on having fun. Joining the server below, you will need to apply for TGMB, if you pass the application you will be faced with a set of tryouts, although that is explained more thoroughly in the Recruitment Center. https://discord.gg/4DaUVVNs56 https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/744113129188884540/822187236032381008/0.1.tgmb.png?
